1
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:03,600
Every physics student has done this:

2
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:07,000
memorize a formula, plug in numbers…

3
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:09,600
…and get an answer

4
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:12,760
you don't actually understand.

5
00:00:12,760 --> 00:00:15,700
Real labs are expensive —

6
00:00:15,700 --> 00:00:18,860
most of us never touch one.

7
00:00:18,860 --> 00:00:21,200
So we built a physics lab

8
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:23,200
that lives in your browser.

9
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:26,240
Physics you can actually touch.

10
00:00:26,240 --> 00:00:29,000
Any browser, a real physics lab.

11
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:31,720
No account, no setup.

12
00:00:31,720 --> 00:00:35,200
Under the hood:

13
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:38,800
real physics engines,

14
00:00:38,800 --> 00:00:40,900
RK4 integration,

15
00:00:40,900 --> 00:00:42,920
true orbital mechanics.

16
00:00:42,920 --> 00:00:45,000
Not fake animations — the real deal.

17
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:47,300
Here's what makes it different.

18
00:00:47,300 --> 00:00:50,500
First: predict.

19
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:54,300
Commit to an answer before it runs.

20
00:00:54,300 --> 00:00:57,000
Will it land here, or here?

21
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:00,500
Then: experiment.

22
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:04,500
Adjust the parameters —

23
00:01:04,500 --> 00:01:06,800
angle, velocity —

24
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:09,000
run the real simulation.

25
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:12,000
And finally: understand.

26
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:16,500
Meet Axion, our AI tutor.

27
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:20,000
Not a generic textbook answer —

28
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:24,000
it reads your numbers

29
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:27,500
and your prediction,

30
00:01:27,500 --> 00:01:31,440
and explains exactly why.

31
00:01:31,440 --> 00:01:33,640
Projectile motion is just the start.

32
00:01:33,640 --> 00:01:36,600
Pendulum — harmonic motion.

33
00:01:36,600 --> 00:01:39,560
Collisions — conservation laws.

34
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:42,800
And my favorite —

35
00:01:42,800 --> 00:01:46,000
orbital mechanics, in full 3D.

36
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:51,600
Same loop every time:

37
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:53,000
predict, experiment, understand.

38
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:56,000
That's how real intuition gets built —

39
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:59,000
accessible to anyone with a browser.

40
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,400
For free. Built for DHS Hacks.

41
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:04,000
Live at axiom-studio20.vercel.app

42
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:07,200
Thanks for watching.
